step1: Create the separate anaconda enviroment.
        conda create -n linearapp python==3.6.9
step2: Install the requirements file
        pip install -r requirements.txt
step4: Intialise your project as git project ( git is used for heroku depolyment)
 Window user : righ click on where project file and click on git bash here
            1) intialize the git : git init
            2)start tracking the files : git add .
            3) check the file present : git status
            4) keep the copy of the file with you so it will show the changes: git commit -m "initial commit"
step3: create a file name as procfile
           (there should not be any extension for this proc file)
            (p should be capital)
step5:start tracking all the project files
        git add .
        git status


